SIMPLE: twining
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Twining
<hw>Twin"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Winding around
something; twisting; embracing; climbing by winding about a support;
<as>as, the hop is a <ex>twining</ex> plant</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twining</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Twining
<hw>Twin"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>The act of one who, or that which,
twines; <fld>(Bot.)</fld> the act of climbing spirally.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twink</ent>⟦br⟧
